  biography in 1957 , hawkins was playing at shreveport , louisiana clubs , and although his music was influenced by the new rock and roll style of elvis presley and the guitar sounds of scotty moore , hawkins blended that with the uniquely heavy blues sound of black louisiana artists for his recording of his swamp - rock classic , " susie q. " fellow louisiana guitarist and future rock and roll hall of famer james burton provided the signature riff and solo .

